data.content:
The root cause is that .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1**. Here are the breaking changes and fixes:

---

### 1. `OpenApiAny` types removed
`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Use `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode` instead.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any;
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// ✅ New
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

---

### 2. `Nullable` property removed
OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` array, not a boolean. `OpenApiSchema.Type` is now a `[Flags]` enum `JsonSchemaType`.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// ✅ New
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
```

---

### 3. Reference model replaced with typed reference classes
Setting a `Reference` property on `OpenApiSecurityScheme` is gone. Use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference` from `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`.

```csharp
// ❌ Old
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};

// ✅ New
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
```

---

### Full corrected code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of changes:**
| What broke | Why | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `OpenApiString` / `OpenApiAny` | Replaced by `JsonNode` | `JsonValue.Create(...)` |
| `Schema.Nullable` | OpenAPI 3.1 uses type array | `Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme.Reference` | Dedicated reference types | `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("id")` |
